INSERT INTO "GW_Volunteers__Volunteer_Job__c" VALUES(1,'False','United States','Salesforce Ranch','','','','','Foster/Adopt','Individuals','<p>Volunteers are needed to help care for and exercise our therapy horses. Our organization is dedicated to helping individuals with disabilities and special needs through equine-assisted therapy, and we rely on the support of volunteers like you to keep our horses happy and healthy.</p><p><br></p><p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Type of Task:</strong></p><p>As a volunteer, you will be responsible for weekly exercise, cleaning stalls, and bathing the horses. This may include leading the horses on walks or in the arena, grooming and tacking them up, and assisting with basic medical care. You will also help maintain the barn area, including mucking stalls and sweeping the barn aisle.</p><p><br></p><p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Skills Needed:</strong></p><p>To be a successful volunteer for this opportunity, you should have a passion for working with horses and helping others. You should also be comfortable working around large animals and be physically fit enough to complete tasks such as lifting hay bales and cleaning stalls. Some previous experience with horses is preferred, but not required.</p><p><br></p><p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Expectations:</strong></p><p>Volunteers will be expected to commit to a regular schedule, and may need to work independently or with a small team. You should also be comfortable taking direction from staff and following safety guidelines at all times. Prior to starting, you will receive training on basic horse care and handling, as well as an orientation to our facility and program.</p><p style="text-align: justify;">This is a unique and rewarding opportunity to make a positive impact on the lives of individuals with special needs while working with animals. If you are passionate about horses and helping others, please consider applying to be a volunteer for our therapy horse program.</p>','True','','False','Burlington','<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Quisque diam risus, fermentum facilisis eros eget, auctor lacinia dui</strong>. </p><p style="text-align: justify;">Mauris nec rhoncus dui. Interdum et malesuada fames ac ante ipsum primis in faucibus. Interdum et malesuada fames ac ante ipsum primis in faucibus. Donec eleifend varius lorem ut consectetur. Etiam non porta augue. Mauris condimentum sagittis ligula bibendum laoreet. </p><p style="text-align: justify;"><br></p><p style="text-align: justify;"><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Cras dapibus elit at lacus euismod viverra ac porttitor felis</strong>. </p><p style="text-align: justify;">Class aptent taciti sociosqu ad litora torquent per conubia nostra, per inceptos himenaeos. Etiam semper dui quis tellus hendrerit mollis. Orci varius natoque penatibus et magnis dis parturient montes, nascetur ridiculus mus. Praesent tellus nulla, rhoncus ac vulputate a, varius ac sem. Quisque suscipit eleifend viverra. Proin sed lorem eget sapien volutpat accumsan quis quis metus. Etiam leo arcu, molestie quis hendrerit vitae, ultricies non sem.</p><p><br></p>','5 Wall St','01803','MA','True','Manual Labor','America/Chicago','Adopt a Therapy Horse','/file-asset-public/FlowToolKit_VolunteerHorseTherapy','','4');
INSERT INTO "GW_Volunteers__Volunteer_Job__c" VALUES(2,'True','United States','Salesforce Tower Pet Project','','','','','Organizational Support','Individuals','<p>If you love animals and want to make a difference in their lives, then this volunteer opportunity at the Pet Adoption Center is perfect for you! We are looking for compassionate and dedicated individuals to help us walk dogs, clean kennels, and greet new dog foster families.</p><p><br></p><p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">As a volunteer at the Pet Adoption Center, you will have the opportunity to:</strong></p><ul><li>Walk and exercise dogs to keep them healthy and happy</li><li>Clean and sanitize kennels to maintain a safe and comfortable environment for the animals</li><li>Greet new dog foster families and provide them with information about our adoption process</li><li>Assist with events and fundraising activities to help support our mission</li></ul><p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Check-in and What to Expect:</strong></p><ul><li>Check-in begins 15 minutes before the start time.</li><li>Please arrive on time, dressed appropriately, and ready to work.</li><li>You will receive training on how to handle and care for the animals.</li><li>You will work as part of a team and be assigned specific tasks and responsibilities.</li><li>The volunteer shift lasts approximately 2-3 hours.</li></ul><p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Qualifications and Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Must be at least 18 years old.</li><li>Must have a love for animals and a desire to make a difference in their lives.</li><li>Must be able to follow safety guidelines and handle animals in a responsible manner.</li><li>Must be able to work in a team-oriented environment and take direction from staff.</li></ul><p style="text-align: justify;">This is a rewarding opportunity to make a difference in the lives of animals and help them find loving forever homes. Join us and become a part of our Pet Adoption Center volunteer team today!</p>','