INSERT INTO "GW_Volunteers__Volunteer_Job__c" VALUES(8,'False','United States','City of Chicago','','','','','Foster/Adopt','Groups','<p>We are seeking volunteers to adopt and commit to maintaining Eastwood Hills park by committing to weekly cleanups and maintenance tasks. As a volunteer, you will play an important role in keeping the park clean, safe and enjoyable for all visitors. This is a great opportunity for individuals, families, and groups to make a direct impact on their community and the environment.</p><p><br></p><p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Tasks:</strong></p><ul><li>Commit to weekly cleanup and maintenance tasks</li><li>Clean up trash and debris in the park</li><li>Maintain flower beds and green spaces</li><li>Report any maintenance issues to the park management</li><li>Follow any park rules and regulations</li><li>Attend periodic meetings with other park adopters</li></ul><p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Skills needed:</strong></p><ul><li>Attention to detail and a sense of responsibility</li><li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team</li><li>Comfortable working outdoors and able to handle various maintenance tools</li><li>Good communication skills and the ability to report any issues to park management</li><li>A passion for community service and making a difference</li></ul><p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">We provide:</strong></p><ul><li>Comprehensive training on maintenance and cleanup procedures</li><li>Supplies and equipment needed for park maintenance</li><li>Ongoing support and communication from park management</li><li>Opportunities to learn about the environment and community engagement</li><li>Opportunities to meet new people and work in a team environment</li></ul><p style="text-align: justify;">This is a great opportunity to make a direct impact on your community and the environment. If you are passionate about community service and want to make a difference, we encourage you to apply for this opportunity. Please ema