INSERT INTO "GW_Volunteers__Volunteer_Job__c" VALUES(10,'False','United States','City of Chicago','','','','','Foster/Adopt','Groups','<p><strong style="font-size: 22px;">Adopt a City Park</strong></p><p><span style="font-size: 14px;">is a volunteer opportunity for individuals who are passionate about preserving the beauty and cleanliness of our city&#39;s parks. As a volunteer, you will have the opportunity to help maintain the park by picking up trash, maintaining trails and grounds, and performing other necessary tasks to keep the park in pristine condition.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Potential Tasks and Roles:</strong></p><ol><li><span style="font-size: 14px;">Picking up trash: Volunteers will be responsible for walking through the park and picking up any litter or debris left behind by visitors.</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px;">Maintaining trails and grounds: Volunteers will be responsible for keeping the trails and grounds clear of debris, fallen branches, and other hazards that may pose a risk to visitors.</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px;">Gardening and landscaping: Volunteers will have the opportunity to help beautify the park by planting flowers, trees, and other plants, as well as maintaining existing gardens and landscapes.</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px;">Other tasks: Depending on the needs of the park, volunteers may also be responsible for performing other tasks such as painting, repairing equipment, or assisting with special events.</span></li></ol><p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Check-in and What to Expect:</strong></p><p><span style="font-size: 14px;">Upon arrival, volunteers will be greeted by the park ranger or volunteer coordinator, who will provide a brief orientation and overview of the day&#39;s tasks. Volunteers will be given gloves, bags, and any necessary tools or equipment for the day&#39;s activities. The park ranger or volunteer coordinator will be available througho